==Arabic==
===Etymology===
From {{ARchar|[[ارتمض]]}} ({{Unicode|artámaɖa}}), ‘to be consumed by grief and sorrow.’ Cf. {{ARchar|[[رمض]]}} ({{Unicode|rámaɖ}}), ‘parchedness,’ ‘scorchedness’; and {{ARchar|[[رمضاء]]}} ({{Unicode|ramɖá:’}}), ‘sun-baked ground.’

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|رَمَضَانُ}}''' {{Unicode|(ramaɖá:n)}} {{m}}

# the ninth month of the Arabic calender
# [[Ramadan]], a time of fasting for Muslims

